article.headline: N.Carolina A&T 81, Norfolk St. 66
article.story: RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Steven Rush scored 18 points to lead five North Carolina A&T players in double figures Thursday as the Aggies defeated Norfolk State 81-66 in the quarterfinals of the Mid-Eastern Atlantic Conference tournament. Jason Wills and Austin Ewing added 11 each, while Greg Roberts and Glenn Nelson chipped in 10 apiece for the third-seeded Aggies (15-16), who led 39-37 at the break. The lead changed 13 times before the Aggies broke away in the second, outscoring the Spartans 42-29 in the half. North Carolina A&T, which shot 44.6 percent for the game, scored 36 points off the bench compared to 17 points by sixth-seeded Norfolk State. Tony Murphy scored a game-high 20 points for Norfolk State, which shot 42.1 percent for the game and hit only 27.8 percent of its 3-point attempts. Calvin Brown finished with 13 points and Michael Deloache had 12. North Carolina A&T will play No. 2 seed Florida A&M in a semifinal game Friday.
